C. Code-Level Fixes
P0: Dedicated Warehouse
# snowflake.yml — change query_warehouse
query_warehouse: OVERWATCH_WH
Create in Snowflake:
CREATE WAREHOUSE IF NOT EXISTS OVERWATCH_WH
  WAREHOUSE_SIZE = 'X-SMALL'
  AUTO_SUSPEND = 60
  AUTO_RESUME = TRUE
  INITIALLY_SUSPENDED = TRUE
  COMMENT = 'Dedicated warehouse for OVERWATCH Streamlit app — isolated cost attribution';
P0: Change execute_as
execute_as: CALLER
Or create a dedicated role:
CREATE ROLE OVERWATCH_APP_ROLE;
GRANT USAGE ON DATABASE DBA_MAINT_DB TO ROLE OVERWATCH_APP_ROLE;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA DBA_MAINT_DB.OVERWATCH TO ROLE OVERWATCH_APP_ROLE;
GRANT IMPORTED PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE SNOWFLAKE TO ROLE OVERWATCH_APP_ROLE;
-- Grant SELECT on specific ACCOUNT_USAGE views rather than blanket IMPORTED PRIVILEGES
P0: Replace global cache clear
# utils/cache.py — replace st.cache_data.clear() with targeted invalidation
def clear_all_cache(
    *,
    clear_streamlit_cache: bool = True,
    clear_metadata: bool = True,
):
    # ... existing session state cleanup ...
    
    if clear_streamlit_cache:
        # Instead of global clear, bump a salt that all cache functions reference
        import uuid
        st.session_state["_refresh_salt_global"] = uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]
        # Do NOT call st.cache_data.clear() — this is global in SiS
P1: Add LIMIT to SQL at generation time
# utils/query.py — add a helper
def _inject_limit(query_text: str, max_rows: int = 5000) -> str:
    """Add LIMIT to queries that don't already have one."""
    upper = query_text.strip().rstrip(';').upper()
    if 'LIMIT' in upper.split('ORDER BY')[-1] if 'ORDER BY' in upper else upper:
        return query_text
    return f"{query_text.rstrip().rstrip(';')}\nLIMIT {max_rows}"
