Summary
The app is architecturally solid — the tiered caching, query telemetry, result guards, admin gating, role-based navigation, and section-level cost attribution are all above-average engineering. The three most urgent fixes are: (1) dedicated warehouse for cost isolation, (2) replacing st.cache_data.clear() with per-section salt invalidation, and (3) changing execute_as: OWNER to a least-privilege pattern. Everything else is medium-priority hardening that reduces hidden credit burn under multi-user load.

